## Cookbook

What follows is some suggested guidance on how to successfully implement the Flywire checkout. However, you should read the documentation fully 
and determine what is appropriate for your use case. If you need to discuss with Flywire please contact your account manager to arrange a call.
This assumes you will be using version `"2"` of the webhook notifications.

1. Configure the checkout with the appropriate parameters ensuring you include values for the `nonce`, `callbackUrl` and `callbackId` and parameters. 
   It often makes sense to use the same value for both the `nonce` and `callbackId`. Set the `callbackVersion`  to `"2"`.

2. When a payer selects a payment option and continues to the payment page an `initiated` [notification](/en/webhooks/notifications-v2/) will be sent 
   to your `callbackUrl`. This includes the payment method (bank_transfer, credit_card, online etc) and additional metadata (varies between methods). 
   For bank transfers it may make sense for you to hold a booking or reserve product as the customer still needs to send Flywire the money to our bank account. 
   We give customers a certain amount of time to do this as indicated by the expiry date in the notification message.

3. When the payer completes the payment then [verify the signature](/en/checkout/implementation/#signature-verification) included in either the `returnUrl` 
   query string or in the args supplied to the `onCompleteCallback` handler. **Perform this verification on your server.** Use this information
   to show the user the appropriate messaging - do not use it to release products or sevices to your customers.

4. Use the status and payment method information returned in the webhook notifications sent to your `callbackUrl` to progress any orders, release
   services, complete bookings etc. This can either be done on `guaranteed` (Flywire has the funds) or `delivered` (Flywire has remitted the funds)
   to your registered bank account. A `cancelled` notification will be sent to you when the booking expires.
